<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="406" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,469,1142]" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,505,530]" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Occipital carina distinctly curved above base of mandible, nearly rectangularly angled with hypostomal carina and connected to hypostomal carina distinctly above base of mandible, resulting in a narrow combined non-lamelliform carina (
<figureCitation box="[550,617,577,602]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acarohelcon varicolor gen. nov. et sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, wings; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; D, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; E, habitus, lateral aspect; F, head, lateral aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
F) and not protruding below base of mandible but adpressed to base of mandible; median lamella of frons absent, only with a weakly developed median carina or crest; frontal depression present but shallow posteriorly; propleuron convex and punctate or rugose; mesopleuron in front of prepectal carina oblique, gradually narrowed (
<figureCitation box="[559,625,685,710]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acarohelcon varicolor gen. nov. et sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, wings; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; D, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; E, habitus, lateral aspect; F, head, lateral aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B); prepectal carina present medio-ventrally; second submarginal cell of fore wing medium-sized (
<figureCitation box="[452,521,721,746]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acarohelcon varicolor gen. nov. et sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, wings; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; D, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; E, habitus, lateral aspect; F, head, lateral aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A); vein a of fore wing only pigmented; marginal cell of hind wing distinctly widened apically (
<figureCitation box="[357,422,757,782]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acarohelcon varicolor gen. nov. et sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, wings; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; D, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; E, habitus, lateral aspect; F, head, lateral aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A); hind coxa with baso-ventral tubercle; hind femur simple, wavy rugose ventrally, rather slender and hardly or not serrate in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[708,775,793,818]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acarohelcon varicolor gen. nov. et sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, wings; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; D, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; E, habitus, lateral aspect; F, head, lateral aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
D); basal part of first metasomal sternite longer than wide and basally smooth, separated from tergite; second metasomal suture between first and second tergites narrow and shallow; second tergite coarsely sculptured and third tergite smooth; fourth-sixth metasomal tergites of 
<specimenCount box="[1356,1377,866,889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="406" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
well exposed behind third tergite; apex of ovipositor sheath with short erect setae but remainder normally obliquely setose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,469,1142]" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1572323482" country="China" county="The" location="It" municipality="Australian" pageId="5" pageNumber="406" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Guangxi" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,973,998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Notes.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus box="[382,430,974,998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">type</typeStatus>
species known from Oriental 
<collectingCountry box="[765,832,973,998]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[846,949,973,998]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
). 
<collectingCounty box="[967,1011,973,998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">The</collectingCounty>
new genus is similar to the 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1320,1437,973,998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Australian</collectingMunicipality>
genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kokujev, 1901" authorityName="Kokujev" authorityYear="1901" box="[223,528,1009,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Parahelcon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[223,354,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Parahelcon</emphasis>
Kokujev, 1901
</taxonomicName>
, if the character of the ventrally sculptured hind femur is ignored. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:ED2587DDFFB4FFF846D7FEC691F2FBCF:60536010FFB4FFF842BDFC1C9625FBB0" box="[1277,1294,1010,1033]" country="China" county="The" municipality="Australian" name="It" pageId="5" pageNumber="406" stateProvince="Guangxi">It</location>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[151,282,1045,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Parahelcon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,282,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Parahelcon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the widened marginal cell of the hind wing (distinctly narrowed in 
<taxonomicName box="[1070,1201,1045,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Parahelcon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1070,1201,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Parahelcon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), vein a of fore wing only pigmented (sclerotized basally) and the occipital flange narrow and adpressed to the base of the mandible (larger and protruding below base of the mandible).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
